JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa recorded a budget deficit of nearly R31 billion ($2.4 billion) in April, the first month of the 2017/18 fiscal year, compared with a shortfall of more than R29 billion over the same period of the 2016/17 fiscal year, Treasury data showed on Friday.The table below shows revenue and expenditure for April, compared with the previous financial year. These are also expressed as a percentage of the 2016/17 budget target and the preliminary outcome for 2017/18.&nbsp;&nbsp;($1 = R12.9504)